cat << EOF
Ksplice is practical technology for updating the Linux kernel without
rebooting. It enables you to avoid the disruptive process of rebooting for
kernel security updates and bugfixes. By making it easy to keep your systems
up to date, Ksplice helps you avoid the security and stability risks of
running out-of-date software.
